gomodel:SYNGO_2525  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Immunoperoxidase labeling for the D3 receptor in the nucleus accumbens of rat brain\"\n- \"Images (a-d) showing that immunoreactivity for D3R, is localized at asymmetric synapses in dendritic spines (ed) in medium-sized spiny neurons of the nucleus accumbens. Note the high density of labeling in, or near, the region of the post-synaptic density at the head of dendritic spines (particularly visible in a sagittal section of a dendritic spine in d), which is juxtaposed to presynaptic terminal profiles (t), containing clear vesicles and forming asymmetric synapses.\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Immunoperoxidase labeling for the D3 receptor in the nucleus accumbens of rat brain.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2525" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

